        <abstract>
            <t>
              This memo presents a technique for utilizing DHCPv4 DNS
              naming information from DHCPv4 requests to supply a DNS
              name for SLAAC enabled hosts.
            </t>
            <t>
              In the IPv4 to IPv6 transition there is a need to
              transparently name a device that may not be using DHCPv6
              also. While SLAAC takes care of supplying an IPv6
              address in many cases, it does not register a name in
              the DNS database by default. By leveraging DHCPv4
              information and suitably using ICMPv6 messages, a DHCPv4
              server can automatically associate the same DNS name
              with the supplied SLAAC address.
            </t>
        </abstract>
